[section Function Adaptors]

Function Adaptor is a higher-order function that takes a "base" __FUNCTION_OBJECT__
and returns an "adapted" __FUNCTION_OBJECT__.
Function Adaptor provides, if possible, two interfaces: A normal higher-order __FUNCTION_OBJECT__, and
an __MPL_METAFUNCTION__ with the corresponding macro for __STATIC_INITIALIZATION__.
An adapted non-local __FUNCTION_OBJECT__ with __STATIC_STORAGE_DURATION__ is __STATICALLY_INITIALIZED__
if the base __FUNCTION_OBJECT__ type is __POD__ and an expression passed to the macro is a /constant expression/.
Also, Function Adaptors don't modify __DEFAULT_CONSTRUCTIBLE__ and __COPY_ASSIGNABLE__-ness of base __FUNCTION_OBJECT__ unless otherwise specified.

[ note If a macro argument is not guaranteed to contain no commas and recursions,
       you must use `BOOST_EGG_XXX_L` and `BOOST_EGG_XXX_R` instead of `BOOST_EGG_XXX`. ]




